::::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 304006005: Config/Level/Mission/3040060/Act/Act304006005.json-->
::::'''Cheerful Garmentmaker:''' The sunlight has not yet faded from Janusopolis... How charming it is. Thanks to you, I'm able to witness this view with my own eyes.
::::'''Cheerful Garmentmaker:''' Pity. I am but a Garmentmaker, not Lady Aglaea herself. Were she here, she'd surely have more to say.
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} You speak differently.
::::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Do Garmentmakers have self-awareness?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_304006405-->
::::'''Cheerful Garmentmaker:''' I apologize if I startled you, dear guest. It wasn't intentional... Compared to other Garmentmakers, I have indeed been imbued with a greater degree of soul essence.
::::'''Cheerful Garmentmaker:''' This place is far too removed from the era we once lived in. Even Lady Aglaea's golden threads cannot reach it. To better fulfill my tasks, I must possess autonomous judgment.
::::'''Cheerful Garmentmaker:''' Aside from myself, other Garmentmakers have also received this blessing &mdash; the Scribe Garmentmaker for instance. We inherited certain talents from Lady Aglaea...
::::'''Cheerful Garmentmaker:''' Ah, it seems I've said too much. Let us return to the matter at hand, dear guest.
